<div style="text-align:center">
<b style="font-size:xx-large; ">Who are we?</b>
<p style="text-align:left">
MitoCanada is Canada only patient advocacy organization for mitochondrial disease, dysfunction and mito-health in general.Active in communities across country, MitoCanada offer patients support and programs , research funding,public education and  awareness campaigns, and advocacy. We relay on individual and corporate support, communities and health care partners to help us carry out our work.
</p>
<b>In pursuit of a cure</b>
<p style="text-align:left">

    Since 2011, the MitoCanada Foundation has proudly supported mitocondrial disease research in Canada, administering more than a half million dollars in reseach in Canada, admistering more than a half million dollars in research grants, awards , and partnerships

</p>
<b>We are Canada's Resource for support , information and education</b>
  <p style="text-align:left">
      For people with mitochondrial disease , their caregivers and family, we provide support, information and education programs. For health providers, we provide support information and resources tp encourage early diagnosis and support and support indiduals and their families throughout the continuum of the diseases

</p>

    <b >The MitoCanada Foundation advocates for change nationally and internationally</b>
  <p style="text-align:left">
     

      Our goal is to collaborate with industry, health system decision-makers, the research community and governments in order to improve the quality of life for people living with mitochondrial diseases. We will work collectively with the international community to make mitochondrial disease a global health priority, raise awareness and increase investments in research.
     

</p>

